label.value: vegetative cell phenotype

value.value: A phenotype that is observed at the level of an individual cell, when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the cell cycle.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: cellular physical quality phenotype during vegetative growth

value.value: A phenotype that affects any physical object quality, such as morphology, number, location, etc., of a cell or a cellular component in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: abnormal subcellular component during vegetative growth

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which the amount, distribution, morphology, or other physical characteristic of a cell part is abnormal in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: altered level of substance in cell during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of a specific substance measured in a cell differs from normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: decreased protein level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of protein measured in a cell is lower than normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal translation or abnormal regulation of translation, but note that changes in protein levels may result from changes in protein stability or degradation as well as changes in protein synthesis. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: altered protein level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of protein measured in a cell differs from normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal translation or abnormal regulation of translation, but note that changes in protein levels may result from changes in protein stability or degradation as well as changes in protein synthesis. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: altered RNA level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell differs from normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. Total RNA or a specific RNA, such as the mRNA transcribed from a gene of interest, may be affected.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype. Also, consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term or its descendants.

label.value: increased protein level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of protein measured in a cell is higher than normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal translation or abnormal regulation of translation, but note that changes in protein levels may result from changes in protein stability or degradation as well as changes in protein synthesis. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal cytoskeleton organization during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which cytoskeleton organization is abnormal in the vegetative growth phase of the cell cycle.

definition.value: Consider annotating to 'abnormal cytoskeleton' (FYPO:0002397), but note that an abnormal cytoskeleton organization process may, but does not necessarily, result in a physically abnormal cytoskeleton.

label.value: decreased level of substance in cell during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of a specific substance measured in a cell is lower than normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: increased level of substance in cell during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of a specific substance measured in a cell is higher than normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: cellular process phenotype during vegetative growth

value.value: A phenotype that affects a cellular process in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: abnormal regulation of translation in response to stress during vegetative growth

value.value: A gene expression phenotype in which regulation of translation in response to stress is abnormal in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: gene expression regulation phenotype during vegetative growth

value.value: A regulation phenotype that affects the regulation of gene expression in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: regulation phenotype during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype that affects the regulation of a molecular function, biological process, or biological quality in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: transcription regulation phenotype during vegetative growth

value.value: A gene expression phenotype that affects the regulation of DNA-dependent transcription in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: transport phenotype during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell process phenotype that affects a transport process in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: localization phenotype during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype that affects the localization of a structure or substance in a cell in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: abnormal nucleus positioning during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which nucleus localization is abnormal in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: abnormal cellular response to starvation during vegetative growth

value.value: A stress response phenotype in which the response to starvation for one or more nutrients is abnormal in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: abnormal cellular response to oxidative stress during vegetative growth

value.value: A stress response phenotype in which a cellular response to oxidative stress is abnormal in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: Use this term if you have assayed the response to oxidative stress at the subcellular or molecular level. If you have assayed growth of cells exposed to oxidative stress in culture, use 'sensitive to oxidative stress' (FYPO:0000726).

label.value: abnormal cellular response to stress during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular response phenotype in which a cellular response to stress is abnormal in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: Use this term if you have assayed the response to a stress at the subcellular or molecular level. If you have assayed growth of cells exposed to the stress in culture, use 'sensitive to stress during vegetative growth' (FYPO:0000304) or 'resistance to stress during vegetative growth' (FYPO:0000850) or a more specific term.

label.value: cellular response phenotype during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype that affects a response to a stimulus in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: abnormal mitotic DNA replication

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which DNA replication is abnormal in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: abnormal mitotic DNA replication initiation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the initiation of nuclear DNA replication is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal DNA recombination during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which DNA recombination is abnormal in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. DNA recombination is a process that results in reassortment of genes, producing gene combinations different from those that were present in the parents.

label.value: DNA metabolism phenotype during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype that affects any DNA metabolic process in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: nucleic acid metabolism phenotype during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype that affects any nucleic acid metabolic process in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: cellular metabolism phenotype during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype that affects metabolism in the cell in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: abnormal microtubule cytoskeleton organization during vegetative growth

value.value: A phenotype that affects the organization of the microtubule cytoskeleton in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. Microtubule cytoskeleton organization is a cellular process that results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising microtubules and their associated proteins.

definition.value: Consider annotating to 'abnormal microtubule cytoskeleton' (FYPO:0002399), but note that an abnormal microtubule cytoskeleton organization process may, but does not necessarily, result in a physically abnormal microtubule cytoskeleton.

label.value: abnormal membrane organization during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which cellular membrane organization is abnormal in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. Cellular membrane organization results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a lipid bilayer membrane, such as the plasma membrane or an organelle membrane.

label.value: abnormal chromatin organization during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which any process of chromatin organization is abnormal in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. Chromatin organization results in the specification, formation or maintenance of the physical structure of eukaryotic chromatin.

label.value: abnormal cellular component organization during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which any process of cellular component organization at the cellular level is abnormal in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: abnormal cellular component assembly during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which any process of cellular component assembly at the cellular level is abnormal in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: decreased vegetative cell population growth

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which the growth of a population of cells is decreased relative to normal in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. Decreased growth may reflect a reduced growth rate (i.e. slower growth), growth that occurs to a lesser extent than normal, or both.

label.value: abnormal vegetative cell population growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is abnormal. Cell population growth refers to an increase in the number of cells in the population as individual cells grow and divide.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype. Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.

label.value: normal vegetative cell population growth

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a population of cells grows normally (i.e. indistinguishably from wild type) in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. Cell population growth refers to an increase in the number of cells in the population as individual cells grow and divide.

label.value: vegetative cell population growth phenotype

value.value: A cell phenotype that affects the rate or extent of cell population growth in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. Cell population growth refers to an increase in the number of cells in the population as individual cells grow and divide.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: decreased amino acid import during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the import of one or more amino acids into the cell occurs to a lower extent than normal in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: abnormal amino acid import during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the import of one or more amino acids into the cell is abnormal in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: abnormal cellular process during vegetative growth

value.value: A phenotype in which a specific cellular process is abnormal in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: abnormal metabolic process during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which a cellular metabolic process is abnormal in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. A metabolic process is any set of chemical reactions and pathways, including anabolism and catabolism, by which living organisms transform chemical substances.

label.value: abnormal actomyosin contractile ring contraction

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which actomyosin contractile ring contraction is abnormal. Contractile ring contraction is the part of cytokinesis in which the actomyosin contractile ring constricts.

label.value: decreased rate of actomyosin contractile ring contraction

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of actomyosin contractile ring contraction is decreased. Contractile ring contraction is the part of cytokinesis in which the actomyosin contractile ring constricts.

label.value: normal actin cytoskeleton organization

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which actin cytoskeleton organization is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Actin cytoskeleton organization is the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising actin filaments and their associated proteins.

label.value: normal cytokinesis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cytokinesis is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Cytokinesis is part of the cell cycle and results in the division of the cytoplasm of a cell and its separation into two daughter cells.

label.value: normal actomyosin contractile ring assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which contractile ring assembly is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: mislocalized actomyosin contractile ring

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell forms an actomyosin contractile ring in an abnormal location. The normal location is at the midpoint of, and perpendicular to, the long axis of the cell.

definition.value: Note that the location of the contractile ring is determined by the location of the cell division site, so an abnormality in cell division site determination can be inferred from this phenotype. Consider also annotating to 'mislocalized septum' (FYPO:0000339) because if the contractile ring forms in an abnormal location, the septum will also do so.

label.value: abnormal protein localization

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein in a cell is abnormal. A protein may be observed in a place where it is not normally found, absent from a place where it is normally found, or both.

definition.value: We recommend using a more specific term if possible. If this term is used, we recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay.

label.value: abolished protein localization to medial cortex

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the medial cortex is abolished.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.
